29/10/2006
NIKSIC, Montenegro -- Police say they twice last week prevented groups of Albanians from crossing the border with BiH illegally. Officials say that on Thursday (October 26th), one group of seven Albanians was detained at Duklo, near the border. On Friday, Niksic police stopped a second group. The Albanians are being returned to their country, while two Montenegrin citizens face charges of human trafficking. (PBS BiH, NTV Hayat, Fena - 28/10/06)
